# Feature Development Rules

## When Creating a New Feature

1. Identify business logic → place in `domain/`
2. Write API/repository calls → place in `data/`
3. Write orchestration hook → place in `hooks/`
4. Page only wires hook + components, no logic
5. Extract repeated UI to `components/shared/` or `lib/`

## Feature Structure (minimal valid)

```
features/<name>/
  pages/     # always needed
  hooks/     # needed if async/state involved
  domain/    # needed if business rules exist
  data/      # needed if API calls exist
  components/ # needed if feature-specific UI exists
  index.ts   # add when other features need to import from here
```

> Not every folder is required. Simple features may only need `pages/` + `components/`.

## Domain Layer Rules

✅ Status configs, filter predicates, stat calculators, format rules  
❌ `useState`, `useEffect`, `navigate`, `toast`, fetch calls

## Hook Layer Rules

- Return stable API: `{ data, isLoading, error, actions }`
- Do not depend on component internals
- Keep one hook per logical concern (avoid monolithic hooks)

## Data Layer Rules

- Only source of API/network access
- Export typed repository functions or query key factories
- Never import from `components/`, `pages/`, or `hooks/`

## Page Layer Rules

- Accept route params, pass to hooks
- Compose layout sections
- No inline filter logic, no direct repo calls
